# WHAT IT IS
#   XGo (formerly Go+) is "a programming language that reads
#   like plain English" — designed simultaneously for
#   engineering, STEM education, and data science.  The XGo
#   tagline:
#       XGo := C * Go * Python * JavaScript + Scratch
#   meaning XGo can call into C/C++ (via cgo), Go (native
#   interop), Python (via the `gopy` bridge), and JavaScript
#   /TypeScript (via the `llgo`/wasm bridges) from a single
#   unified source tree, with a STEM-friendly syntax that
#   shrinks Go's surface even further.  Derived from Go with
#   full Go-engineering-tool compatibility (build, mod, fmt,
#   test, doc, env, install, get all mirror their `go`
#   counterparts).  Source extension `.xgo`; classes are
#   defined in `.gox` files (the compiler ITSELF is written
#   in `.gox` — see `cmd/xgo/*.gox`).
#
#   The toolchain is a single multi-mode binary `xgo` that
#   mirrors the `go` CLI but adds XGo-specific verbs:  `pack`
#   to merge scattered config into a single index pack, `serve`
#   to run an XGo language server (LSP), `watch` to regenerate
#   `.go` files on `.xgo` changes for IDE integration, and a
#   modular `mod` family (`mod init`, `mod tidy`, `mod
#   download`) for module maintenance.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/xgo/main_app.gox +
#                       cmd/xgo/*_cmd.gox subcommand
#                       declarations — written in XGo's own
#                       class-style `.gox` syntax;  extracted
#                       via `gh api repos/goplus/xgo/contents/
#                       cmd/xgo/...`)
#
#   xgo <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Core verbs  (mirroring `go` CLI):
#     build [flags] [PACKAGES]       Build XGo files
#     install [flags] [PACKAGES]     Build XGo files and
#                                    install target to GOBIN
#     run [flags] PACKAGE [ARGS...]  Compile and run an XGo
#                                    program
#     test [flags] [PACKAGES]        Test XGo packages
#     fmt [flags] PATH...            Format XGo packages
#     doc [flags] [PKG-PATH]         Show documentation for
#                                    package or symbol
#     env [flags] [VAR...]           Prints XGo environment
#                                    information
#     get [flags] [PACKAGES]         Add dependencies to the
#                                    current module and
#                                    install them
#     clean [flags] <GOPSRCDIR>      Clean all XGo auto-
#                                    generated files
#     version [flags]                Print XGo version
#     bug                            Start a bug report
#
#   Module maintenance  (`xgo mod <SUB>`):
#     mod init [<MODULE-PATH>]       Initialize a new XGo
#                                    module
#     mod tidy                       Add missing and remove
#                                    unused modules
#     mod download                   Download modules to the
#                                    local cache
#
#   XGo-specific:
#     go [flags] [PACKAGES|FILES]    Convert XGo code into Go
#                                    code (transpiles `.xgo`
#                                    / `.gox` → `.go`)
#     pack [flags] [DIRECTORY]       Merge a project's
#                                    scattered configuration
#                                    files into a single
#                                    index_pack file
#     serve [flags]                  Serve as an XGo
#                                    LangServer (LSP-protocol-
#                                    compliant for editor
#                                    integration)
#     watch [flags] [DIR]            Monitor code changes in
#                                    an XGo workspace and
#                                    regenerate the Go files
#                                    for IDE / tooling
#                                    interop
#
#   Help / version:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#
